The President is pleased to announce that Bill Burns, the Director of the Central Intelligence Agency (CIA), has been invited to serve as a member of the President's Cabinet. The President highlights the importance of good intelligence as America's first line of defense, and Bill Burns has demonstrated this since his first day on the job. Working closely with the Director of National Intelligence, Bill has used intelligence to give the country a strategic advantage. Under his leadership, the CIA has taken a clear-eyed, long-term approach to national security challenges, such as Russia's aggression against Ukraine and competition with China. Bill provides clear and straightforward analysis prioritizing the safety of the American people. He is respected by the CIA and is seen as a leader who represents the best of America. The President looks forward to continuing to work with Bill in the future.